President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Kenneth Charles Canterbury, Jr. to be the Director of the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms, and Explosives. Canterbury is currently the President of the National Fraternal Order of Police and has held the position since 2003. He has a distinguished career in law enforcement, earning the rank of Major in the Horry County Police Department in Conway, South Carolina after 26 years of service. Canterbury has also served on the Executive Board of the National Fraternal Order of Police for over two decades and has been inducted into the South Carolina Law Enforcement Hall of Fame. He is a graduate of Coastal Carolina University.